## Application

**Name:** NileScan CS Knowledge Hub

**Description:**
NileScan is a Node.js web application (built using core modules only) that serves as a computer science article platform. Visitors can browse and read CS articles without an account. Registered users can sign in and out. Authors (a privileged role) can additionally publish new articles directly from the home page. User authentication is simulated using a server-side `session.json` file as specified in the assignment.

---

## Application Features

- **Home Page (`/`)** — Displays all articles as cards sorted newest-first. If the logged-in user is an `author`, a "Publish a New Article" form appears above the article grid. Regular users and guests see only the articles.
- **Article Detail Page (`/article?id=N`)** — Renders the full content of the selected article with title, author, and date. Invalid or missing IDs return a 404 page.
- **Login Page (`GET /login`)** — Sign-in form with username and password fields. Demo credentials are shown on the page.
- **Login Handler (`POST /login`)** — Validates credentials against `data/users.json`. On success, writes `data/session.json` and redirects to home with a welcome flash message. On failure, redirects back to `/login` with an error flash message.
- **Logout (`POST /logout`)** — Deletes `data/session.json`, ending the session. Redirects to home with a confirmation flash message.
- **Create Article (`POST /create`)** — Accepts title and content from the home-page form. Appends a new article object to `data/articles.json` with an auto-incremented ID, the logged-in author's username, and today's date. Restricted to `author` role only.
- **Role-Based Access** — The create form is rendered only for `author` role users. `user` role and guests see no form and cannot POST to `/create`.
- **Flash Messages** — Colour-coded feedback (info / success / error) passed as URL query params and rendered at the top of each page.
- **404 Page** — Rendered for any unknown route or invalid article ID.
- **Input Safety** — All form inputs are trimmed. Required fields are validated. Missing query parameters are handled gracefully. The server never crashes on malformed requests.

